</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
KINCAID, the former British Shipbuilders marine engine builder based at Port
Glasgow on the Lower Clyde, is to cease making engines and concentrate on
making spare parts. Its owner, Kvaerner of Norway, is to cut the workforce
from 280 to 100 in the next few months.
