<TEXT>
MOODY'S Investors Service, the US credit rating agency, has downgraded
CDollars 800m of Canadian Pacific's Ltd senior unsecured debt following last
Monday's announcement by the big conglomerate of a first-quarter loss of
CDollars 5.3m (USDollars 4.6m), or 2 cents a share, writes Robert Gibbens.
