<HEADLINE>
FT  08 MAY 91 / International Company News: Aerospatiale and MBB in joint
helicopter venture
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By WILLIAM DAWKINS
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   PARIS
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
AEROSPATIALE, the French aerospace group, and MBB, the German aerospace
manufacturer, have created a joint venture - Eurocopter International - to
market jointly each others' helicopters.
This is a step towards the full merger of the helicopter businesses of
Aerospatiale and MBB, as agreed in outline last year and passed by the
European Commission competition authorities in February.
The pair have combined sales of FFr10bn (Dollars 1.6bn) - of which 70 per
cent comes from the French partner - making it the world's second largest
helicopter supplier after Sikorski of the US. Aerospatiale has 27 per cent
of world helicopter sales outside the US and the Soviet Union - considered
to be closed markets - while MBB has 4 per cent.
Eurocopter International is a marketing company equally owned by the pair,
and has already started talks on possible civil sales with two Soviet
helicopter design departments.
By the end of the year, Aerospatiale and MBB expect to complete negotiations
on the formation of a holding company, which would pool all their helicopter
activities and be roughly 60 per cent owned by Aerospatiale and 40 per cent
held by the German partner.
MBB, as the smaller partner, will have to make a cash payment to bring its
stake up to that level and may adjust its stake, said Eurocopter officials.
The pair are awaiting the results of independent company valuations before
completing the deal.
</TEXT>
