FT  08 MAY 91 / UK Company News: Upton &amp; Southern falls deeper into the red
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
LOSSES ON its property side left Upton &amp; Southern Holdings, the
Middlesbrough-based retailing and property company, deeper in the red in the
year to January 26.
On turnover of Pounds 11.49m (Pounds 12.5m) pre-tax losses increased from
Pounds 800,000 to Pounds 1.43m.
The property market continued to be depressed and further amounts were
written off to bring development values in line with the market.
Retailing was profitable overall and the department stores continued to show
steady progress.
The auditors again qualified the accounts as to the provisions and work in
progress. They said because of uncertainty in the market they were unable
the state whether the provisions were sufficient or to value the work in
progress.
Interest charges increased to Pounds 665,000 (Pounds 352,000) and there was
a tax credit of Pounds 3,700 (Pounds 254,000). Losses per share came out at
15.76p (6.05p).
