FT  08 MAY 91 / House starts down 14%
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ANDREW TAYLOR, Construction Correspondent
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
THE recent rise in house sales has yet to find its way through to increased
output by house builders, according to figures published yesterday by the
Environment Department.
The number of new homes started by private builders in the three months to
the end of March fell by 14 per cent compared with the corresponding period
last year.
Builders say the improvement in sales has occurred only recently and has
come too late to offset sharply lower sales in January and February. They
have been selling from stock rather than starting new construction in what
remains a fragile market in spite of reductions in interest rates.
The number of new homes started by builders in March fell to 12,600 from
15,400 last year.
