FT  07 MAY 91 / Lloyd's Feltrim probe
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
SUBSTANTIAL losses at the Feltrim underwriting agencies will be the first to
be investigated under a procedure instigated last week by Lloyd's of London,
the insurance mar-ket.
Measures announced last week included the launch of an inquiry whenever a
syndicate's net loss at the end of a three-year accounting period amounts to
150 per cent or more of the amount of premium a syndicate is allowed to
write.
Published figures for losses at Feltrim exceed this ratio, Lloyd's said, but
exact figures for the losses have yet to be established. A meeting of
Feltrim Names - outsiders who back Lloyd's with their personal wealth - is
set for tomorrow.
