compared with BFr96.4bn. The company is proposing to cut its dividend from
BFr129 to BFr100 a share.
The results were also hit by an increase in the debt linked to Wagons-Lits'
stake in Sodexho, the French catering group, which was sold earlier this
year, and reduced margins in the original railway sleeping and dining-car
operations.
