<TEXT>
Stop the carping - it may be time to pass the hat round for Mr Mick
Newmarch. The Pru's remuneration committee has just awarded its new chief
executive a 43 per cent salary rise for his work in 1989, when earnings
advanced 12 per cent and pre-tax profits were 9 per cent ahead.
Next time the committee meets, it will base its calculations on calendar
1990 when earnings plunged by 60 per cent and profits slipped by a third.
Using the same sort of arithmetic, Mr Newmarch may soon be paying his
shareholders to come to the office.
