FT  04 MAY 91 / UK Company News: Prudential chief gets 43% pay increase
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By RICHARD LAPPER
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
MR MICK NEWMARCH, the chief executive of Prudential Corporation, received a
salary almost twice that of the average for other insurance industry chiefs
in 1990.
According to Prudential's latest annual report, he received Pounds 543,673
in 1990, a 43 per cent increase on the previous year's Pounds 379,651.
The pay rise was decided by a committee of non-executive directors and
includes bonus payments based on the company's performance in 1989, when
profits rose by 9 per cent.
The increase makes Mr Newmarch, who also has more than 600,000 share options
and receives other benefits, one of the best paid insurance managers in the
country.
The heads of most leading composite, life companies and brokers received
between Pounds 200,000 and Pounds 300,000 in 1990.
